issue.title: 主键采用snowflake,在新增时出现 `invalid input for query argument $1: '1' ('str' object cannot be interpreted as an integer)`
issue.body:
role model
```
class Role(Base):
    """角色表"""

    __tablename__ = 'sys_role'

    # 允许手工赋值
    id: Mapped[id_key] = mapped_column()
    code: Mapped[str] = mapped_column(sa.String(10), unique=True, comment='角色编码')
    name: Mapped[str] = mapped_column(sa.String(20), unique=True, comment='角色名称')
    status: Mapped[int] = mapped_column(default=1, comment='角色状态（0停用 1正常）')
    sort: Mapped[int] = mapped_column(default=999, comment='排序')
    is_filter_scopes: Mapped[bool] = mapped_column(default=True, comment='过滤数据权限(0否 1是)')
    remark: Mapped[str | None] = mapped_column(UniversalText, default=None, comment='备注')
```  

自己做的一个初始化过程，保存时出错 `invalid input for query argument $1: '1' ('str' object cannot be interpreted as an integer)`
调整 schema 中的方法，注释掉以下方法，正常
```
class SchemaBase(BaseModel):
    ....

    # if PrimaryKeyType.snowflake == settings.DATABASE_PK_MODE:
    #     from pydantic import field_serializer

    #     # 详情：https://fastapi-practices.github.io/fastapi_best_architecture_docs/backend/reference/pk.html#%E6%B3%A8%E6%84%8F%E4%BA%8B%E9%A1%B9
    #     @field_serializer('id', check_fields=False)
    #     def serialize_id(self, value: int) -> str:
    #         return str(value)
```
